    {
      "type": "add",
      "id": "78ce4182269116bc",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "78ce4182269116bc",
        "text": "The manner in which associations are built within digital notetaking apps look nice and pretty. They create nifty-looking graphs and visualizations. However, such tools are not structured in a way to optimize learning. Antinets, on the other hand, are built entirely around association. You cannot install a note in the Antinet without associating it with the neighboring notes. As a result a chain-reaction takes place in the system. All notes are essentially chain-linked to every other note in the system. This is the concept of associative chaining, which I detail later in this book."
      },
